12月10日，俄罗斯有50多个城市爆发示威活动，数万民众涌上街头抗议普京领导的统一俄罗斯党在杜马选举中舞弊，要求重新选举及结束普京的统治，这成为自[[苏联解体|苏联解体]]以来俄规模最大的示威活动。反对党派通过社交网站[[facebook|facebook]]和[[twitter|twitter]]呼吁民众参加行动来表达不满，在[[莫斯科|莫斯科]]有近5万人冒着暴风雪响应，他们从下午2时开始聚集在市中心附近的广场高喊“要求公平选举”的口号和高举着海报，广场周围部署了5万名军警，还有[[直升机|直升机]]在广场上空盘旋。[[圣彼得堡|圣彼得堡]]有1万人上街游行，呼吁废除这次选举结果并重新投票。在俄远东最大城市[[海参崴|海参崴]]，超过1000名<ref>{{cite web |author=11:39AM GMT 10 Dec 2011 |url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/europe/russia/8947954/Russia-election-protests-begin-in-Vladivostok.html |title=Video: Russia election protests begin in Vladivostok |publisher=Telegraph |date= |accessdate=11 December 2011 |archive-date=2011-12-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111215202112/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/europe/russia/8947954/Russia-election-protests-begin-in-Vladivostok.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>民众在街道上示威并高喊“普京是个[[虱子|虱子]]！”等口号，有人还举个一个画上统一俄罗斯党党徽和写有“这些鼠辈们应该滚蛋！”的布条<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.zaobao.com/photoweb/pages3/protest111211.shtml |language= |title=抗议选举舞弊 俄50城市示威倒普京 |publisher=联合早报 |date=2011-12-11 |accessdate= |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111211041950/http://www.zaobao.com/photoweb/pages3/protest111211.shtml |archivedate=2011-12-11 }}</ref>。在[[新西伯利亚|新西伯利亚]]有3,000人<ref>{{cite web |author=Daniel Sandford |url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-16122524 |title=BBC News - Russian election: Biggest protests since fall of USSR |publisher=Bbc.co.uk |date= |accessdate=11 December 2011 |archive-date=2014-04-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140427083141/http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-16122524 |dead-url=no }}</ref>、[[葉卡捷琳堡|葉卡捷琳堡]]有4,000人集会抗议<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/europe/russia/8947840/Russian-protests-live.html |title=Russian protests: live |publisher=Telegraph |date=31 May 2011 |accessdate=11 December 2011 |archive-date=2014-01-09 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140109114019/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/europe/russia/8947840/Russian-protests-live.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。其他城市如<ref>http://www.reuters.com/article/2011/12/09/us-russia-idUSTRE7B610S20111209?feedType=RSS&feedName=topNews&rpc=71|agency {{Wayback|url=http://www.reuters.com/article/2011/12/09/us-russia-idUSTRE7B610S20111209?feedType=RSS&feedName=topNews&rpc=71%7Cagency |date=20190822101200 }} Reuters|date01/12/11|access10/12/11</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.voanews.com/english/news/Moscow-Braces-for-Anti-Putin-Rally-135313948.html|work=Voice of America|date=9/12/11|title=Pro-Democracy Protests Put Putin, Russia at Turning Point|access-date=2011-12-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120418194651/http://www.voanews.com/english/news/Moscow-Braces-for-Anti-Putin-Rally-135313948.html|archive-date=2012-04-18|dead-url=yes}}</ref> [[加里寧格勒|加里寧格勒]]、[[托木斯克|托木斯克]]<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.nytimes.com/2011/12/11/world/europe/thousands-protest-in-moscow-russia-in-defiance-of-putin.html |title=存档副本 |accessdate=2011-12-11 |archive-date=2020-12-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201218220709/https://www.nytimes.com/2011/12/11/world/europe/thousands-protest-in-moscow-russia-in-defiance-of-putin.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>、[[鄂木斯克|鄂木斯克]]<ref name="barentsobserver1">{{cite web |author=Text: Thomas Nilsen |url=http://www.barentsobserver.com/election-fraud-protests-in-murmansk-and-arkhangelsk.4997162-16174.html |title=Election fraud protests in Murmansk and Arkhangelsk |publisher=BarentsObserver |date=2004-05-26 |accessdate=11 December 2011 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120406191515/http://www.barentsobserver.com/election-fraud-protests-in-murmansk-and-arkhangelsk.4997162-16174.html |archivedate=2012-04-06 }}</ref>、[[阿尔汉格尔斯克|阿尔汉格尔斯克]]、[[摩爾曼斯克|摩爾曼斯克]]<ref name="barentsobserver1"/>、[[克拉斯諾亞爾斯克|克拉斯諾亞爾斯克]]、[[庫爾干|庫爾干]]<ref name="barentsobserver1"/>、[[彼尔姆|彼尔姆]]、[[卡累利阿|卡累利阿]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.aljazeera.com/news/europe/2011/12/2011121053755418485.html |title=Anti-Putin protests erupt across Russia - Europe |publisher=Al Jazeera English |date=4 October 2011 |accessdate=11 December 2011 |archive-date=2014-04-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140427110458/http://www.aljazeera.com/news/europe/2011/12/2011121053755418485.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>、[[哈巴罗夫斯克|哈巴罗夫斯克]]<ref>{{cite web |author=Lee Moran |url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-2072427/Russian-protests-2011-Vladimir-Putins-louse-say-demonstrators-alleged-election-fraud.html |title=Russian protests 2011: 'Vladimir Putin's a louse' say demonstrators over alleged election fraud | Mail Online |publisher=Dailymail.co.uk |date= |accessdate=11 December 2011 |archive-date=2011-12-11 |archive-url=https://archive.is/20111211072835/http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-2072427/Russian-protests-2011-Vladimir-Putins-louse-say-demonstrators-alleged-election-fraud.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>、[[喀山|喀山]]<ref>{{Cite news| last = May| first = Robert| title = Hundreds Protest Election Results| work = The Kazan Herald| location = Kazan| accessdate = 2011-12-11| date = 2011-12-10| url = http://kazanherald.com/2011/12/10/hundreds-protest-election-results/| deadurl = yes| archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20120426040307/http://kazanherald.com/2011/12/10/hundreds-protest-election-results/| archivedate = 2012-04-26}}</ref>、[[下诺夫哥罗德|下诺夫哥罗德]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://theopenglobe.org/wiki/Russia_sees_largest_protests_since_fall_of_Soviet_Union |title=Thousands continue protest in Moscow following elections |publisher=OpenGlobe |date=6 December 2011 |accessdate=11 December 2011 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120406044439/http://theopenglobe.org/wiki/Russia_sees_largest_protests_since_fall_of_Soviet_Union |archivedate=2012-04-06 }}</ref>與[[海參崴|海參崴]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www2.cna.com.tw/ShowNews/Detail.aspx?pNewsID=201112100259&pType1=PF&pType0=aOPL&pTypeSel=0&pPNo=2|title=全俄掀抗議潮 挑戰普京統治|publisher=中央社|date=10 December 2011|accessdate=12 December 2011|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151001064055/http://www2.cna.com.tw/ShowNews/Detail.aspx?pNewsID=201112100259&pType1=PF&pType0=aOPL&pTypeSel=0&pPNo=2|archivedate=2015-10-01}}</ref>等地都有抗议活动的发生。在西伯利亚城市[[彼尔姆|彼尔姆]]的一场示威活动中15人被捕。在远东城市[[哈巴罗夫斯克|哈巴罗夫斯克]]，在一起未经批准的游行集会中有30人被捕。当天总计全国有100人被捕，大多数发生在莫斯科以外<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.mirror.co.uk/news/latest/2011/12/10/mass-rallies-demand-putin-quits-115875-23626125/ |title=Mass rallies demand Putin quits |publisher=mirror.co.uk |date=11 August 2009 |accessdate=11 December 2011 |archive-date=2011-12-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111217214801/http://www.mirror.co.uk/news/latest/2011/12/10/mass-rallies-demand-putin-quits-115875-23626125/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

